## How Long Does SEO Take for Oxford Businesses?

**Months 1–3** — Technical foundations: indexation fixes, Core Web Vitals, structured data, Google Business Profile optimisation.

**Months 3–6** — Initial ranking improvements as topical authority content indexes. Measurable traffic increases for mid-competition Oxford and Oxfordshire queries.

**Months 6–12** — Compound growth as authority builds across topic clusters. Competitive Oxford queries in professional services, biotech, and property begin yielding page-one positions.

## How Much Does an SEO Consultant in Oxford Cost?

**Technical audits** — £500–£1,200 depending on site size and scope.

**Topical maps** — from £800 to £2,500+ depending on industry complexity and topic breadth.

**Monthly retainers** — from £1,500. Independent consultant pricing typically delivers the same senior-level quality as an Oxford or London agency at 40–60% of the cost. Initial consultations are free.

